{
  "title": "Type-Checking CLI Tools Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide demonstrates how to use FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs, to type-check command-line interface (CLI) tools in Python 3.12+.",

  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI is not only for REST APIs but can also be used for CLI tools.",
    "It provides powerful type validation and fast performance, making it ideal for CLI tools.",
    "We'll use FastAPI's router functionality to create our CLI tool."
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, CommandLineInterface\napp = FastAPI()\ncli = CommandLineInterface(app)\n# Define your CLI commands here\n# ...\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    cli.run_from_args()\n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n# Example of a command with parameters\n@cli.command('mycommand')\ndef mycommand(param1: int, param2: str):\n    # Handle the command logic here\n    pass\n```"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "The examples provided are using FastAPI version 0.79.0 and Python 3.12.0."
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "While FastAPI is powerful for CLI tools, it might be overkill for simple command-line utilities.",
    "Remember to install the necessary dependencies using pip:\n`pip install fastapi[all] uvicorn`"
  ]
}
